earch and development: a search for systems from the viewpoint of research and technology organizations,”  International Journal of Innovation and Technology Management,7(3),263-272,2010.[31] Lin, M.C., C.C. Wang, M.S. Chen and C.A. Chang, “Using AHP and TOPSIS approaches in customer-driven product design process,” Computers in Industry,59(1), 17-31,2008.[32] Nordhaus, W., “An economics theory of technological changes,” American Economic Review, 59(2) ,18-28,1969.[33] Saaty, T.L., The Analytic Hierarchy Process. McGraw-Hill , New York, U.S., 1980.[34] Su, K.J., “An R&D management model for MNCs' subsidiaries: an empirical study of European affiliates in Taiwan,” International Journal of Management and Decision Making ,3(3/4),353-369,2002.[35] Shih, H.S., H.J. Shyur and E.S. Lee, “An extension of TOPSIS for group decision making,” Mathematical and Computer Modelling, 45(7-8),801-813,2007.[36] Tsaur, S.H., T.Y. Chang and C.H. Yen, “The evaluation of airline service quality byfuzzy MCDM,” Tourism Management, 23(2),107-115,2002.[37] Thomas, V.J., S. Sharma and S.K. Jain, “Using patents and publications to assess R&D efficiency in the states of the USA,” World Patent Information ,33(1) 4-10,2011.[38] Zhang, A., Y. Zhang and R. Zhao, “A study of the R&D efficiency and productivity of Chinese firms,” Journal of Comparative Economics,31,444–464,2003.[39] Zeleny, M., “A Concept of Compromise Solutions and the Method ofthe Displaced Ideal,” Computers and Operations Research,1,479-496,1974.
